Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.25,0:09:55.26,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even made him hook it up in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.26,0:09:56.49,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That pitiful computer president.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.96,0:09:58.31,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had completely forgotten about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:00.40,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.40,0:10:02.44,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.44,0:10:03.49,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Kimidori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:04.94,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.94,0:10:06.59,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,As client number one...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.59,0:10:09.33,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,...you get your problem solved free of charge as a bonus!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.63,0:10:11.41,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were planning on charging people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.66,0:10:19.22,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:21.56,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you so readily accept her request...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.56,0:10:23.60,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we can't solve her problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.68,0:10:26.07,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.07,0:10:30.39,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,That president's probably just cooped up with two-month late freshman blues.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.39,0:10:34.69,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to march into his room, smack him around a few times, and drag him back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.69,0:10:36.28,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She seems to seriously believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.91,0:10:40.01,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But if the president has someone like Kimidori-san for a girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.01,0:10:41.24,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...why would he shut himself in his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.81,0:10:44.83,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you friends with Kimidori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.13,0:10:48.29,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I never talked to her until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:52.07,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She could have taken her problem to a teacher or the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.07,0:10:52.85,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.85,0:10:55.04,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She already talked to them but was ignored...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:57.72,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...so she came to see the SOS Brigade?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:10:59.96,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.96,0:11:03.18,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Haruhi seems to see this as an opportunity to attract bigger cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:05.78,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and solve every last one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.45,0:11:09.69,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a good idea to pass out flyers by the front gate again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.09,0:11:12.39,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The president's residence...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.39,0:11:16.31,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...was a studio apartment located in an everyday commonplace...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.31,0:11:18.82,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...three-story building looking neither old nor new.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.42,0:11:21.41,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.64,0:11:24.83,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:29.02,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if there's a way to open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.63,0:11:31.13,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It should be the other way around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:34.64,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we circle around to the balcony in the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:37.14,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be able to get in if we smash the glass, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.31,0:11:40.13,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,This room is on the third floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:43.24,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,...and we aren't some youth gang of career burglars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.24,0:11:44.85,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want a criminal record yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.16,0:11:46.22,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.22,0:11:48.82,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go talk to the landlord and ask for a key.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.82,0:11:51.68,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,If we say that we're concerned friends, he'll lend it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.68,0:11:53.60,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You sure use that story a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:12:01.09,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She stared at me with eyes like liquid helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.46,0:12:03.18,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.18,0:12:04.36,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,It was open?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:05.74,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:06.76,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.76,0:12:08.16,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.54,0:12:10.78,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably hiding under his bed or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.78,0:12:12.76,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll drag him out and capture him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:15.64,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Apparently, she doesn't feel a single atom of guilt...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.64,0:12:17.21,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...about plundering his computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:22.40,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:25.90,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured he'd be scrunched up into a ball in some corner hugging his knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.44,0:12:27.17,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.17,0:12:31.23,HaruhiDefault,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know anywhere else to find someone suffering from a two-month late case of freshman blues?
